The paper proposes a new generalization bound for domain adaptation and introduces two models for multiple source domain adaptation using adversarial neural networks. The paper also conducts experiments on real-world datasets related to sentiment analysis, digit classification, and vehicle counting. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
